  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disability support - tribal child in Pachamalai TN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ilavarasan, ten years old, is Mallika&apos;s son. They belong to the Malayali tribe residing in the remote villages in the reserve forests of Pachamalai hills in Tamil Nadu. He is a specially-abled child. Since both of his parents are tribal peasants, they could not afford medical attention catering to his unique needs. This project aims to provide shelter for Ilavarasan at a care center in Tiruchirapalli, the nearest city, to support his medical expenses, education, and vocational training.</narrative>
  </description>
